  <description>
   <![CDATA[
    <p>WADI is an acronym of 'Web Application Distribution
    Infrastructure'.</p>

    <p>WADI's aim is to resolve many of the problems of dealing with
    state in the clustered J2EE Web Tier. This involves technologies
    such as :</p>

    <ul>
    <li>Simple HttpSession semantics and a guaranteed resolution to
    application vs container space concurrency issues within the
    HttpSession</li>
    <li>HttpSession Migration (inter-node and node-store-node)</li>
    <li>HttpRequest relocation (by redirection and proxying)</li>
    <li>Pluggable/Stackable HttpSession persistance mechanisms (File, Database, etc.)</li>
    <li>NYI - pluggable HttpSession state replication strategies - in-vm, db, file etc..</li>
    <li>NYI - pluggable self-partitioning, self-healing clustering substrate.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>WADI can currently be plugged into the following J2EE web
    containers:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>Tomcat 5.1.28+</li>
    <li>Jetty 5.1.3+</li>
    </ul>

    <p>WADI is currently undergoing a major rearchitecture. New
    documentation is being entered into the
    <a href="http://docs.codehaus.org/pages/listpages-dirview.action?key=WADI">WADI WIKI</a>
    . We hope to have a 2.0 release out shortly.</p>

    <p>Please browse our <a href="./faq.html">FAQ</a> for further detail.</p>

